<chapter xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    version="5.0" xml:id="FEEHELP">
    <title>FEE-HELP</title>
    <section>
        <title>FEE-HELP</title>
                <para>There are a couple of extra fields in the VET tab of a contact record that need to be
            answered if the student is applying for VET FEE-HELP. You will need to mark the checkbox
            called 'VET FEE-HELP eligible' for them to appear, these are:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Citizenship status</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Tax file number</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="80%" contentdepth="80%"
                    fileref="images/vet_fee_help_contact.png"/>
            </imageobject>
            <caption>
                <para>VET FEE-HELP fields in a Contact record</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>There are also a couple of extra fields in the VET tab of a class record that need to be
            answered if the class is eligible for VET FEE-HELP. You will need to mark the checkbox
            called 'This is a VET FEE-HELP eligible class' for them to appear, these are:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Type of attendance</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Census date</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Reporting period</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Equivalent full-time student load</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="80%" contentdepth="80%"
                    fileref="images/vet_fee_help_class.png"/>
            </imageobject>
            <caption>
                <para>VET FEE-HELP fields in a Class record</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>Every enrolment record will have a VET FEE-HELP tab that is used when the
            corresponding enrolment has has FEE-HELP from the government. There are a number of
            fields that need to be filled in, with other just being read only. The fields that can
            be edited are:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Fee Subsidy</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit offered value</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit used value</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>RPL Indicator</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit Field of Education ID</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit offered provider code</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit type</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit provider type</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Credit level</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="80%" contentdepth="80%"
                    fileref="images/vet_fee_help_enrolment.png"/>
            </imageobject>
            <caption>
                <para>VET FEE-HELP tab in a Enrolment record</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>   
        <para>To peform a VET FEE HELP export you need to open the class list window. Once you have
            this open, highlight one or more classes, click on the cogwheel and choose the option
            VET FEE HELP export.</para>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%"
                    fileref="images/vet_fee_help_export.png"/>
            </imageobject>
            <caption>
                <para>Performing a VET FEE-HELP export</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>   
        <para>After you run the VET FEE-HELP export, you can open the reporting tool 'HEPCAT' and
            upload the data to get lodged. </para>
        <para>This tool will allow you to validate the data obtained in the VET FEE-HELP
            export.</para>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%"
                    fileref="images/hepcat.png"/>
            </imageobject>
            <caption>
                <para>Where the export files get lodged and validated</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>   
    </section>
</chapter>
